<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MESSAGE OF 'SEALS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
While Feigen has fought against the stereotypes women are burdened with, she 
has not discovered that men are also the victims of society's most violent 
stereotypes. 
</P>
<P>
Does she care that some young men will see "Navy SEALS" and decide that they 
must join so they can prove their worth? Does she care that innocent women and 
children would undoubtedly be killed in an attack such as depicted in "Navy 
SEALS"? No. She only cares that the one white woman in the film is depicted 
well. 
</P>
<P>
DON HAYASHI 
</P>
<P>
Culver City 
