<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOVIET BOLSHOI BALLET TO GIVE 7 S.D. SHOWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EILEEN SONDAK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Soviet Bolshoi Ballet will appear in seven performances at the San Diego 
Civic Theatre from Aug. 21-26. The troupe's weeklong stay is part of the 
company's first American tour since the 1960s. 
</P>
<P>
While the 56 dancers are here, they will perform recent productions of 
"Giselle" and "Swan Lake," two of the greatest full-length Russian ballets in 
the repertory. 
</P>
<P>
On opening night, Aug. 21, "Swan Lake" will star Nina Ananiashvili as 
Odette/Odile and Alexei Fadeyechev as Prince Siegfried. The performance begins 
at 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
On Aug. 22, Nina Semizorova and Yuri Vasyuchenko will appear in the same roles, 
and on Aug. 23, Ludmila Semenyaka and Alexei Fadeyechev will star. All 
performances begin at 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Following those three performances, the Bolshoi will present its only 
California staging of "Giselle," in four weekend performances. On Aug. 24 at 8 
p.m., the role of Giselle will be danced by Nina Semizorova, and Alexander 
Vetrov will be Count Albrecht. The performance will be repeated Aug. 25 at 2 
p.m. with Nina Ananiashvili and Alexi Fadeyechev, and at 8 p.m with Alla 
Mikhalchenko and Yuri Vasyuchenko. 
</P>
<P>
Nina Semizorova and Mark Peretokin will play the roles Aug. 26 at 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
All performances will be danced to a live orchestra. 
</P>
<P>
Seats are available at the Civic Theatre box office, or by calling 236-6510 or 
278-TIXS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
