<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ON WEEKEND TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The first National Football League preseason games of 1990 and a quartet of 
games matching the Dodgers and Angels against their Northern California rivals 
highlight a busy sports schedule on television this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
The Raiders are among six teams beginning NFL preseason action before the 
league's 22 other teams. 
</P>
<P>
The nomadic squad is in London for the American Bowl. The New Orleans Saints 
provide the opposition for Sunday's 10 a.m. game on Channels 4, 36 and 39. 
</P>
<P>
Two NFL games are on tap today. The Chicago Bears face the Cleveland Browns in 
the AFC/NFC Hall of Fame game at 10 a.m. on Channels 7, 3, 10 and 42. Another 
American Bowl matches the Denver Broncos and Seattle Seahawks in Tokyo at 7 
p.m. on ESPN. 
</P>
<P>
All three contenders in the suddenly revived National League West pennant race 
make Southland television appearances over the weekend. The third-place Dodgers 
take on the second-place Giants at 12:15 p.m. today on Channels 2 and 8 and 
Sunday at 12:30 p.m on KTTV Channel 11. The first-place Cincinnati Reds meet 
the San Diego Padres at 4 p.m. today and at 11:15 a.m. Sunday on Channels 42 
and 51. 
</P>
<P>
The Angels play host to the American League West-leading Oakland Athletics in 
SportsChannel games at 7 tonight and 1 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The Goodwill Games concludes its 17-day run with telecasts beginning at 12:05 
p.m. and 5:05 p.m. Sunday on cable station TBS. Meanwhile, the U.S. men's 
basketball team, beaten by both the Soviet Union and Yugoslavia in the Goodwill 
Games, gets a rematch against the Soviet Union at 1 p.m. today on Channels 4, 
36 and 39 as both teams prepare for the world championships later this month. 
STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</TEXT>
