<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TEEN-AGER KILLED, 2ND HURT IN GANG SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A teen-ager was shot to death and another was critically wounded Friday in a 
gang-related shooting in the middle of a Hollywood intersection, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The identities of the dead and injured teens were not released. 
</P>
<P>
Detective James Leahy said the shootings occurred about 7:30 a.m. after two 
gang members surprised a pair of rival gang members in the middle of the 
intersection of Gower Street and Fountain Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
One of the gang members fired on the other two in an attack witnessed by about 
20 people, Leahy said. Police arrested two suspects in the assault, a 
15-year-old boy and a 17-year-old youth. Their names were not released because 
of their ages. 
</P>
