<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MURDERER SEIZED AFTER 3 YEARS AS FUGITIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Convicted murderer Kenneth (Kendog) Evans, a South- Central street gang member 
who escaped from Los Angeles County Central Jail more than three years ago, was 
returned this week from Atlanta, where he was arrested for breaking into a car. 
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old fugitive escaped on Feb. 5, 1987, by switching identification 
wrist bands with a fellow prisoner who was ready for release. 
</P>
<P>
When the man's name was called, Evans stepped forward and walked out of jail. 
</P>
<P>
At the time, Evans was awaiting sentencing for the 1985 slaying of a gang rival 
shot in a drive-by attack. Evans was brought back to Los Angeles on Thursday by 
members of the sheriff's fugitive detail and placed in a jail section reserved 
for high-security risks. 
</P>
