<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY STARS PLAY TEAM FROM L.A. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego County will be going for its fourth consecutive victory tonight 
against other just-graduated high school players in the Southern California 
College Prep All-Star Football game at Mira Mesa High School. 
</P>
<P>
The game matches 40 of the best local players against a team mostly made up of 
players from the Los Angeles City Section. 
</P>
<P>
Organizers allowed Los Angeles to draw from Southern Section teams within the 
city's boundary to make the game more equitable. 
</P>
<P>
Among local players scheduled to participate are Point Loma quarterback Danny 
White and his favorite receiver, teammate Brett Callan. 
</P>
<P>
White was the county's leading passer, completing 144 of 239 attempts for 2,522 
yards and 21 touchdowns last year. He averaged 252.2 yards per game. 
</P>
<P>
Callan was the county's leading receiver with 59 receptions and a 17.5 
yards-per-catch average. 
</P>
<P>
White will go to Penn State, Callan to California. 
</P>
<P>
Among the others competing for San Diego are Oceanside running back Terry 
Vaughn (Arizona), who led the county with 166.2 yards per game. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego's offense will be coached by Ramona's Mel Galli; Southwest's Carl 
Parrick coaches the defense. They will be joined by Point Loma's Bill Settles 
and Lincoln's Roy Reed. 
</P>
<P>
Kickoff is at 7:30 p.m. Tickets are $6 for adults, $4 for students with ID and 
$2 for children under 12. MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
