<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: MCGUIRE, YOUNG TO PLAY BASEBALL IN 3-COUNTRY SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ryan McGuire of El Camino Real High and Dmitri Young of Rio Mesa are among 18 
high school baseball players selected to represent the United States in a 
three-country tournament in Japan. 
</P>
<P>
The event, sponsored by the Japan National High School Baseball Federation, 
will be held Aug. 19-Sept. 2 at various locations in Japan. An all-star team 
representing Korea also will compete. 
</P>
<P>
Former Pepperdine Coach Dave Gorrie will coach the U. S. team. 
</P>
