<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
McDonald's to Help East German Farmers: Up against a campaign to stop its Big 
Mac hamburger from crossing the crumbling Berlin Wall, McDonald's Corp. 
promised to help East Germany's farmers by buying their produce. 
</P>
<P>
A West German supplier of the fast-food giant has signed a deal with a 
cooperative farm near Magdeburg, close to the East German border, McDonald's 
Germany Chairman Walter Rettenwender said. East German politicians want to ban 
McDonald's and similar fast-food firms, saying their throwaway plastic cartons 
will cause huge disposal problems. But McDonald's is hoping that opinion will 
change as it helps bolster East Germany's sagging agricultural industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
