</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 14-year old girl was fatally shot and her brother and boyfriend were 
seriously wounded in an apparent gang-related shooting when their car stopped 
for traffic signal in Pomona Friday evening, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
Maryann Ayala was driving the auto and the two others were passengers when two 
to four other youths who had apparently followed them from from a convenience 
store pulled alongside in a car and started firing, Pomona Police Lt. Joe 
Romero said. 
</P>
<P>
The girl, her brother, Armando Ayala, 17, who was seated in the rear, and her 
boyfriend, Daniel Salazar, 18, who was in the passenger seat, all were hit in 
the left side, Romero said. 
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate indication whether the girl or the other victims were 
gang members. 
