<TEXT>
<P>
A Butte County judge contends he has no conflict of interest even though his 
wife is half owner of an alcohol-awareness school to which he sentences 
convicted drunk drivers. About 500 convicted drivers annually pay up to $845 to 
attend the Prevention Education Program Inc., the only school of its kind in 
the rural Northern California county. Court officials estimate that North Butte 
County Municipal Judge Darrell W. Stevens has sentenced 250 convicted drunk 
drivers to the school since he was appointed to the bench by Gov. George 
