<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROBERT J. SCHMORLEITZ; ATTORNEY DEFENDED UNITARIAN CHURCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robert J. Schmorleitz, 77, an attorney who represented the First Unitarian 
Church when its nonprofit status was jeopardized during the anti-communist 
investigations of the 1950s. 
</P>
<P>
Schmorleitz went to court to help the church keep its nonprofit status after 
Unitarian leaders refused to sign a loyalty oath declaring that they weren't 
communists. Schmorleitz received his law degree from Southwestern University in 
Los Angeles and after World War II service in the Merchant Marine set up a 
private law practice in North Hollywood. In Los Angeles on July 26 of cancer. 
</P>
