<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
WORKSHOP SLATED ON RE-ENTERING COLLEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange Coast College will hold a free workshop for people who want to re-enter 
college after a break in their academic careers. 
</P>
<P>
The two-hour workshop is designed for people who want to make career changes or 
learn new job skills. It will be held Aug. 15 from 6 to 8 p.m. in the Re-Entry 
Center, behind the college's Counseling and Admissions Building. 
</P>
<P>
The college is at 2701 Fairview Road. For information, call (714) 432-5162. 
</P>
</TEXT>
