<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
EX-SUPT. TO FILL POST TEMPORARILY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Saddleback Community College District Board of Trustees has named former 
district superintendent Robert A. Lombardi as vice superintendent of employee 
relations and personnel. 
</P>
<P>
Lombardi, who served as superintendent from 1974 to 1982, has been hired 
temporarily to replace Maria Sheehan, who transferred to the state headquarters 
of the community college system in Sacramento to serve as a vice superintendent 
in charge of faculty and staff diversity. 
</P>
<P>
During his tenure as superintendent, Lombardi directed the opening of Irvine 
Valley College. Following his resignation in 1982, Lombardi, a 16-year Irvine 
resident, pursued a career in the private sector in educational software. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
SADDLEBACK COMMUNITY COLLEGE DISTRICT; SCHOOL ADMINISTRATORS; HIRINGS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
